This paper is primarily focused on understanding the nature of bug fixing in software repositories and applying that knowledge to automated program repair. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses abstract syntax tree differencing and probabilistic repair models, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mathematical reasoning on the search space of automated repair and the time to navigate through it can be considered as systems and control (cs.SY) or machine learning (cs.LG).
